				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Disabling sprite rendering while leaving background rendering enabled, or disabling background rendering while leaving sprite rendering enabled, has no effect on the operation of the PPU's rendering. It just blocks the pixels from hitting the compositor stage. In order to have an effect, you need to disable both.
<br />
<br />Once the PPU is decapped properly, we might be able to add a Visual 2C02 to our Visual 2A03 and puzzle out exactly why this $#!+ happens.</div>

